   147‚Üí * `Pattern<a>` is the generic type for patterns matching a value of type `a`. A pattern can be any (nested) javascript value.
   148‚Üí *
   149‚Üí * They can also be wildcards, like `P._`, `P.string`, `P.number`,
   150‚Üí * or other matchers, like `P.when(predicate)`, `P.not(pattern)`, etc.
   151‚Üí *
   152‚Üí * [Read the documentation for `P.Pattern` on GitHub](https://github.com/gvergnaud/ts-pattern#patterns)
   153‚Üí *
   154‚Üí * @example
   155‚Üí * const pattern: P.Pattern<User> = { name: P.string¬Ý}
   157‚Üíexport type Pattern<a = unknown> = unknown extends a
   158‚Üí  ? UnknownValuePattern
   159‚Üí  : KnownPattern<a>;
